          Glassell Park doesn't need much introduction to people who live there —
          it's a neighbourhood that works, that has character, and that doesn't
          make a big deal about itself. The hillside streets above the LA River
          have homes from the 1940s and 1950s sitting alongside newer construction.
          The flats off San Fernando Road have a mix of single-family homes and
          multi-family buildings that have been here for generations.
        </p>
        <p>
          What we bring to Glassell Park is the same thing we bring to every
          northeast LA neighbourhood: same-day service, OEM parts, and technicians
          who give you a written estimate before touching anything. No dispatch
