            ice maker has been gradually producing less over the past few months —
            not a sudden stop but a slow decline — mineral scale on the water inlet
            valve is the most likely cause in 90065. Older homes with original
            galvanized supply lines compound the LADWP mineral content. Replacing
            your in-door filter every 6 months (not 12) helps meaningfully with
            this water supply.
          </div>
        </div>
